WEBVTT

00:00.191 --> 00:02.106
These communities are perfect
for what we're envisioning.

00:02.149 --> 00:04.238
Previously on
"The Walking Dead"...

00:04.282 --> 00:06.066
Man: Alexandria was
a self-sustaining

00:06.110 --> 00:07.763
ecological community.

00:07.807 --> 00:09.635
We got the plans from the leader
of an allied community,

00:09.678 --> 00:11.245
Maggie Rhee.

00:11.289 --> 00:13.769
Why do you trust
these people?Daryl: Who says we do?

00:13.813 --> 00:16.033
It's good to see Alexandria
getting cleaned up, though.

00:16.076 --> 00:18.905
You sure don't want
to come with us?

00:18.948 --> 00:21.125
Lance, are we good?Everything's fine.

00:21.168 --> 00:22.604
Pamela's on board.

00:22.648 --> 00:24.606
In fact, we're gonna bring
even more people in.

00:24.650 --> 00:27.087
[Walkers snarling]We are going
to remake the world.

00:30.308 --> 00:32.875
[Walkers growling]

00:56.073 --> 00:58.336
[Arrow whistling]

00:59.598 --> 01:00.903
What are we at?

01:00.947 --> 01:02.253
Eight to nine.

01:02.296 --> 01:03.732
So...

01:03.776 --> 01:05.517
still winning.

01:05.560 --> 01:07.519
For about
10 more seconds.

01:11.653 --> 01:13.873
You, too?

01:13.916 --> 01:15.266
Yeah.

01:15.309 --> 01:16.919
I just
talked to Maggie.

01:16.963 --> 01:18.443
What'd she say?

01:18.486 --> 01:19.792
Not much.

01:19.835 --> 01:22.316
Just gave me this.

01:22.360 --> 01:24.579
Directions to the nearest
Commonwealth checkpoint.

01:24.623 --> 01:27.147
Troopers left them in case
people changed their minds.

01:27.191 --> 01:29.367
Yeah.
A lot of people are.

01:29.410 --> 01:30.977
Yeah...

01:33.197 --> 01:34.546
You'll be back,
though.

01:34.589 --> 01:35.851
Right?

01:35.895 --> 01:37.766
Yeah,
I think so.

01:44.208 --> 01:45.818
Okay.

01:51.476 --> 01:52.738
Hey!

01:52.781 --> 01:55.828
Shoot your shot!

01:55.871 --> 01:57.438
You need an escort?

02:00.876 --> 02:03.140
Why?

02:03.183 --> 02:04.967
It's a long walk,
you know?

02:05.011 --> 02:07.579
Might get bored.
That's all.

02:09.972 --> 02:11.713
Um...

02:11.757 --> 02:13.933
[Horse neighing in distance]

02:16.544 --> 02:19.286
We got
a rider coming!

02:19.330 --> 02:21.332
Who is it?

02:21.375 --> 02:25.292
♪

02:25.336 --> 02:27.947
Nobody we know.

02:27.990 --> 02:30.602
Marco:
Hold where you are!

02:30.645 --> 02:32.952
Hold, or we will shoot!

02:32.995 --> 02:42.614
♪

02:42.657 --> 02:52.493
♪

02:52.537 --> 02:56.149
[Coughs]

02:56.193 --> 02:58.412
♪

02:58.456 --> 02:59.979
He's been shot!
Get help!

03:00.022 --> 03:01.894
[Groans]

03:01.937 --> 03:03.896
Devils...

03:03.939 --> 03:05.289
They're slaughtering them.

03:05.332 --> 03:08.335
♪

03:08.379 --> 03:10.207
Liars...

03:10.250 --> 03:18.127
♪

03:18.171 --> 03:21.696
You've got to go...

03:21.740 --> 03:24.873
Yes.

03:24.917 --> 03:34.883
♪

03:34.927 --> 03:44.893
♪

03:44.937 --> 03:54.903
♪

03:54.947 --> 04:04.913
♪

04:04.957 --> 04:14.923
♪

04:14.967 --> 04:23.280
♪

04:30.330 --> 04:32.289
We're not going.

04:32.332 --> 04:34.552
Maggie, he died
begging for our help.

04:34.595 --> 04:35.944
I understand it.

04:35.988 --> 04:38.686
But we're barely holding on
as it is.

04:38.730 --> 04:40.427
Someone we know
must've sent him.

04:40.471 --> 04:42.168
Could be from the Commonwealth,
or Georgie --

04:42.211 --> 04:43.865
Or it could be
a trap.

04:43.909 --> 04:46.433
We go to help and leave
the Hilltop open to attack.

04:46.477 --> 04:48.566
I don't think
it's a trick.

04:48.609 --> 04:50.176
He was scared.
He wasn't lying.

04:50.219 --> 04:51.612
Even if he wasn't,

04:51.656 --> 04:53.353
we can't go up
against another group

04:53.397 --> 04:54.528
without the people
to fight them.

04:54.572 --> 04:56.095
We don't have that.

04:56.138 --> 04:58.663
What happened to taking in
whoever was in need?

04:58.706 --> 05:00.665
Being outnumbered has never
stopped you before.

05:00.708 --> 05:02.928
Maybe it should have.

05:02.971 --> 05:06.279
♪

05:06.323 --> 05:09.326
We're barely holding on.

05:09.369 --> 05:13.112
It sounds like
these people are, too.

05:13.155 --> 05:15.244
That's exactly
who my mother would've targeted,

05:15.288 --> 05:16.507
and I helped.

05:16.550 --> 05:18.683
I'm not letting it happen
to someone else.

05:18.726 --> 05:21.076
♪

05:21.120 --> 05:22.774
So you're not leaving.

05:22.817 --> 05:24.079
I am.

05:24.123 --> 05:25.385
I'm just...

05:25.429 --> 05:27.344
I have to help
these people first.

05:27.387 --> 05:37.354
♪

05:37.397 --> 05:47.364
♪

05:47.407 --> 05:56.982
♪

05:57.025 --> 05:59.941
♪

05:59.985 --> 06:01.813
You take over
at the halfway mark.

06:01.856 --> 06:06.121
♪

06:06.165 --> 06:07.427
Hershel: Mom!

06:07.471 --> 06:10.952
Mom!

06:10.996 --> 06:14.173
How long this time?

06:14.216 --> 06:15.957
What do I always
tell you?

06:16.001 --> 06:18.264
As long as it takes.That's right.

06:18.307 --> 06:20.571
You're gonna hold down the fort
while I'm gone?

06:20.614 --> 06:29.449
♪

06:29.493 --> 06:31.973
[Truck doors close]

06:32.017 --> 06:34.498
Keep a perimeter,
stay on alert.

06:34.541 --> 06:37.196
You got it.
Good luck.
Thank you.

06:37.239 --> 06:39.198
♪

06:39.241 --> 06:41.592
Could you get that
for me?

06:41.635 --> 06:49.251
♪

06:49.295 --> 06:51.776
Why don't you want
their help?

06:51.819 --> 06:54.300
The Commonwealth's.

06:57.259 --> 07:00.175
Because we can get by
without it.

07:00.219 --> 07:01.960
Why do we have to
just "get by"?

07:02.003 --> 07:05.485
It's only temporary.

07:05.529 --> 07:07.531
What's easier
isn't always better.

07:19.456 --> 07:20.935
You know,
before the Fall,

07:20.979 --> 07:23.808
I lived on a farm
with my family and my dad.

07:23.851 --> 07:26.027
One day,
these corporate farm developers

07:26.071 --> 07:27.333
started knocking
on our door,

07:27.376 --> 07:29.509
trying to
buy us out.

07:29.553 --> 07:31.772
My dad
kept saying no.

07:31.816 --> 07:34.296
Then, one day,
this bad drought hit.

07:34.340 --> 07:37.169
The developers started
knocking again,

07:37.212 --> 07:38.649
except this time,
they offered three times

07:38.692 --> 07:40.085
what the farm
was worth.

07:40.128 --> 07:42.261
They knew we were in debt
and desperate.

07:42.304 --> 07:45.482
But they also knew
the drought would end

07:45.525 --> 07:48.006
and the farm would become
profitable again,

07:48.049 --> 07:50.312
and all they had to do
was outlast us.

07:50.356 --> 07:52.880
They start dropping off
crates of food to "help"

07:52.924 --> 07:54.578
with the livestock.

07:54.621 --> 07:57.102
And he would just let it
sit there on the porch and rot

07:57.145 --> 07:58.886
so they'd see it
when the next shipment came.

07:58.930 --> 08:01.759
He said that
we were being tested.

08:01.802 --> 08:03.021
And guess what happened.

08:03.064 --> 08:05.545
The drought ended.

08:05.589 --> 08:08.113
We got
back on our feet.

08:08.156 --> 08:11.682
And those developers
never bothered us again.

08:13.771 --> 08:15.729
Why'd your dad
let the food rot?

08:15.773 --> 08:17.078
If they'd
seen us take it,

08:17.122 --> 08:19.080
they would've known
we needed them

08:19.124 --> 08:20.560
and never
left us alone.

08:20.604 --> 08:22.867
But the cattle
were hungry.

08:22.910 --> 08:24.608
We didn't lose any.

08:24.651 --> 08:28.263
We stuck together,
and we made it through.

08:28.307 --> 08:30.396
Yeah,
you "got by."

08:33.921 --> 08:36.315
It's just...

08:36.358 --> 08:38.447
"Getting by" is
what I've been forced to do

08:38.491 --> 08:39.884
my whole life.

08:39.927 --> 08:43.191
I was told that it makes you
stronger and wiser.

08:43.235 --> 08:45.237
But it doesn't.

08:45.280 --> 08:46.760
It hurts.

08:46.804 --> 08:49.546
What would you
have done?

08:49.589 --> 08:51.939
♪

08:51.983 --> 08:54.638
Asked everyone
what they wanted

08:54.681 --> 08:57.249
instead of
deciding for them.

08:57.292 --> 08:58.903
Is that
what I'm doing?

08:58.946 --> 09:01.122
You think The Commonwealth
knows better?

09:01.166 --> 09:02.559
Is that
crazy to think?

09:02.602 --> 09:04.125
Yes.

09:04.169 --> 09:07.346
Those people have not
been tested for 10 years.

09:07.389 --> 09:09.566
Do you wanna be there
when they are?

09:09.609 --> 09:15.746
♪

09:15.789 --> 09:18.139
I just...

09:18.183 --> 09:20.577
want things to be the same
every day.

09:20.620 --> 09:30.587
♪

09:30.630 --> 09:31.979
♪

09:32.023 --> 09:33.677
Do you agree?

09:33.720 --> 09:37.463
♪

09:37.506 --> 09:41.206
With most of it,
yeah.

09:41.249 --> 09:44.601
Whoa!
Look out![Tires screech]

09:44.644 --> 09:49.083
♪

09:49.127 --> 09:52.391
[Walkers growling]

09:52.434 --> 10:02.401
♪

10:02.444 --> 10:07.841
♪

10:07.885 --> 10:10.235
Knife slashed right
through the neck guard.

10:10.278 --> 10:15.022
♪

10:15.066 --> 10:16.633
Shot between
the armor gaps.

10:16.676 --> 10:18.635
Man: Hey!

10:18.678 --> 10:23.640
♪

10:23.683 --> 10:25.816
Maggie!

10:25.859 --> 10:30.864
♪

10:30.908 --> 10:33.824
It's Aaron.

10:37.741 --> 10:45.444
♪

10:45.487 --> 10:47.838
Gabriel: But not only is it
borne of hate,

10:47.881 --> 10:52.843
but from love and
from friendship, and from fear.

10:52.886 --> 10:57.195
And in Luke 15:12, Christ speaks
of a rich father's wayward son

10:57.238 --> 11:00.024
that selfishly set off
to distant lands,

11:00.067 --> 11:05.333
who squandered his riches
on decadence and wild living.

11:08.075 --> 11:10.687
And then, the son
found his soul empty.

11:12.079 --> 11:14.125
And he was in need.

11:14.168 --> 11:17.868
And he went back to his father
and begged for forgiveness.

11:17.911 --> 11:20.218
And his father embraced him,

11:20.261 --> 11:24.309
for his son "was dead,
and is now alive.

11:24.352 --> 11:27.312
He was lost, and now is found."

11:27.355 --> 11:31.838
Now, there were a lot
of stunned faces

11:31.882 --> 11:34.319
when I asked all of you
to sit by a stranger today,

11:34.362 --> 11:35.668
and I'm still seeing
a lot of awkwardness

11:35.712 --> 11:37.148
with the arrangement.

11:37.191 --> 11:41.543
A lot of stiff backs,
clenched butt cheeks.

11:41.587 --> 11:44.895
[Laughter]

11:44.938 --> 11:46.897
Why?

11:46.940 --> 11:49.856
Those of you that were out there
in the wasteland,

11:49.900 --> 11:51.510
you know from
the people you found,

11:51.553 --> 11:53.468
from the ones
you could rely upon,

11:53.512 --> 11:55.993
that it didn't matter that
you were strangers beforehand,

11:56.036 --> 11:57.646
did it?

11:57.690 --> 12:00.519
You were forced to see
the humanity in each other,

12:00.562 --> 12:02.303
and though not bound by blood,

12:02.347 --> 12:08.222
these strangers became more than
friends, they became family.

12:08.266 --> 12:11.704
Why is it that way out there...

12:11.748 --> 12:14.576
but not that way in here?

12:14.620 --> 12:15.795
♪

12:15.839 --> 12:17.884
Romans 3:23 --

12:17.928 --> 12:21.583
"For all have sinned and
fall short of the glory of God."

12:21.627 --> 12:25.762
Now let me repeat that --
"All of us have sinned."

12:25.805 --> 12:28.939
And that is the very thread
that binds us together.

12:28.982 --> 12:31.942
And if you strip yourselves
of the superficial labels --

12:31.985 --> 12:38.383
what do we do, where do I live,
how much money do I have --

12:38.426 --> 12:39.906
if you strip yourselves of that,

12:39.950 --> 12:42.343
it will make you see
the person by your side

12:42.387 --> 12:44.868
as you see yourself
in the mirror.

12:44.911 --> 12:48.262
And the way we were
before the world fell

12:48.306 --> 12:51.526
cannot be the way we are
moving forward.

12:51.570 --> 12:54.051
We must always
remember the thread,

12:54.094 --> 12:56.618
for that is what makes us try,

12:56.662 --> 13:01.188
it makes us forgive,
it makes us return from peril.

13:01.232 --> 13:04.148
It makes us...

13:04.191 --> 13:06.106
us.

13:06.150 --> 13:08.326
♪

13:08.369 --> 13:10.676
Sounds like you're blowing smoke
up my ass.

13:10.719 --> 13:12.156
No, you were great.

13:12.199 --> 13:14.027
I -- I was expecting

13:14.071 --> 13:16.421
a little more
fire and brimstone,

13:16.464 --> 13:18.815
I guess.

13:18.858 --> 13:20.991
You look happy.

13:21.034 --> 13:23.210
I think I might be.

13:23.254 --> 13:25.386
So all that up there,
that was...

13:25.430 --> 13:27.780
No, it's, uh --
it's not an act.

13:27.824 --> 13:29.564
I mean,
in the beginning,

13:29.608 --> 13:31.349
I was just going through
the motions,

13:31.392 --> 13:33.394
but then, one day,
I just wasn't.

13:33.438 --> 13:37.311
It was like
a switch was flipped,

13:37.355 --> 13:40.184
and I could
hear Him again.

13:40.227 --> 13:42.447
Yeah.

13:42.490 --> 13:43.883
That hell
we went through,

13:43.927 --> 13:48.192
it almost feels like
it wasn't real.

13:48.235 --> 13:50.847
Like it was just a nightmare
or something.

13:54.459 --> 13:56.722
What about Alexandria?

13:56.765 --> 13:59.768
Oh, Commonwealth's pouring
even more manpower

13:59.812 --> 14:01.727
and resources
into the rebuild.

14:01.770 --> 14:05.818
But, uh, while that's getting
finished up,

14:05.862 --> 14:08.647
they've asked me to,
uh, help out

14:08.690 --> 14:12.390
with their new
immigration initiative.

14:12.433 --> 14:15.436
They didn't seem too keen
on immigrants when we came in.

14:15.480 --> 14:17.699
They weren't.

14:17.743 --> 14:19.136
And after they heard
that I worked

14:19.179 --> 14:20.615
for an NGO
back in the day,

14:20.659 --> 14:23.444
they asked me to review
their intake policies.

14:23.488 --> 14:24.881
Now we're reaching out

14:24.924 --> 14:26.491
and bringing in people
that need help.

14:26.534 --> 14:27.927
The Lord's work.

14:27.971 --> 14:31.061
Yeah.

14:31.104 --> 14:34.064
Actually,
that's, um...

14:34.107 --> 14:36.457
That's why I'm here.

14:36.501 --> 14:39.112
There's a group
of about 40 people

14:39.156 --> 14:40.461
holed up
in an apartment complex

14:40.505 --> 14:42.550
on the western border
of Virginia.

14:42.594 --> 14:44.074
We want
to make first contact

14:44.117 --> 14:45.945
and offer them help.

14:45.989 --> 14:48.905
Some of the folks upstairs,
um...

14:48.948 --> 14:51.516
they thought it'd be a good idea
if you tag along.

14:51.559 --> 14:53.431
Why me?

14:53.474 --> 14:55.520
It's a...

14:55.563 --> 14:58.740
religious group,
so...

14:58.784 --> 15:00.525
Any hostiles
in the territory?

15:00.568 --> 15:02.266
We'll have troops with us,
just in case.

15:02.309 --> 15:04.181
Also, my boss, Carlson,
will be with us.

15:04.224 --> 15:05.965
He's a little,
um...

15:06.009 --> 15:07.488
Well, you'll see,
but...

15:07.532 --> 15:08.881
his heart's
in the right place.

15:08.925 --> 15:11.492
Jesse: Uh, sorry to interrupt,
uh...

15:11.536 --> 15:13.103
Carlson's ready
when you are.

15:13.146 --> 15:15.105
Oh.
Thank you, Jesse.

15:15.148 --> 15:17.542
♪

15:17.585 --> 15:20.284
New kid.
We're training him.

15:20.327 --> 15:23.243
♪

15:23.287 --> 15:25.898
What do you say?

15:25.942 --> 15:27.987
What do you know
about these people?

15:28.031 --> 15:29.946
According to the scouts,
they're, uh,

15:29.989 --> 15:32.078
just a friendly group
of settlers.

15:32.122 --> 15:39.738
♪

15:39.781 --> 15:42.306
God,
do you feel that?

15:42.349 --> 15:44.743
That rush?

15:44.786 --> 15:47.746
That mix of dopamine
and adrenaline, just...

15:47.789 --> 15:49.574
[Grunts]

15:49.617 --> 15:53.360
[Laughs]

15:53.404 --> 15:56.668
It's just,
that anticipation...

15:56.711 --> 15:59.627
We're gonna
change lives.

15:59.671 --> 16:01.412
You.

16:01.455 --> 16:02.761
And you.

16:02.804 --> 16:04.893
And even
you, too, Jesse.

16:04.937 --> 16:07.200
Today, we're gonna make
the world

16:07.244 --> 16:09.507
just a little bit better
than it was yesterday.

16:09.550 --> 16:12.553
I thought you said these were
"friendly settlers."

16:12.597 --> 16:15.643
That doesn't
look friendly.

16:15.687 --> 16:17.254
You don't think so?

16:17.297 --> 16:18.951
No.

16:18.995 --> 16:20.170
Okay.

16:20.213 --> 16:21.649
What if they aren't?

16:21.693 --> 16:23.173
Hmm?

16:23.216 --> 16:24.391
If they're angry,

16:24.435 --> 16:26.219
that just means
they're afraid.

16:26.263 --> 16:30.180
When they meet you,
they won't be.

16:30.223 --> 16:32.834
Man,
I cannot wait

16:32.878 --> 16:34.880
to watch you two
do your thing.

16:39.798 --> 16:42.105
Is he going
in with us?

16:42.148 --> 16:44.063
He usually does,
yeah.

16:44.107 --> 16:46.022
But he's not gonna do
any of the talking.

16:46.065 --> 16:47.675
And we'll have
backup nearby.

16:47.719 --> 16:49.460
You sure?

16:51.418 --> 16:52.941
Hey!

16:52.985 --> 16:54.595
Are they
setting up camp?

16:54.639 --> 16:55.857
That they are.

16:55.901 --> 16:57.816
So they're
not coming with us?

16:57.859 --> 17:00.340
Well...

17:00.384 --> 17:02.516
better not
spook the natives.

17:02.560 --> 17:04.214
But don't worry.

17:04.257 --> 17:07.608
They're just
a chirp away.

17:07.652 --> 17:10.829
Sergeant Crowe,
do you copy?

17:10.872 --> 17:13.571
Over.

17:13.614 --> 17:15.094
Copy, sir.

17:15.138 --> 17:16.661
Over.

17:16.704 --> 17:18.097
You see?

17:18.141 --> 17:21.448
It's all good!

17:21.492 --> 17:23.711
Yeah,
I'm not doing this.

17:23.755 --> 17:25.844
Places like that usually have
some old man

17:25.887 --> 17:28.064
with a shotgun inside
just looking for an excuse

17:28.107 --> 17:31.415
to kill some dumbass
who stepped on his front lawn.

17:31.458 --> 17:33.852
Practically screams
"do not disturb."

17:33.895 --> 17:35.201
Yeah.

17:35.245 --> 17:36.637
I agree.

17:36.681 --> 17:38.683
Hey!
Is everything alright?

17:38.726 --> 17:41.338
Aaron: We're not so
sure about this.

17:41.381 --> 17:43.340
Might be better
to leave them alone.

17:43.383 --> 17:45.342
Abort?

17:45.385 --> 17:47.909
Just because of some
pre-game jitters?

17:47.953 --> 17:49.955
No, because your plan
is shit,

17:49.998 --> 17:51.130
and I don't want
to die.

17:51.174 --> 17:53.089
That's all.

17:53.132 --> 17:54.916
I've done it before.

17:54.960 --> 17:56.875
We'll do it again.

17:56.918 --> 17:59.225
What's the largest group
you've found?

18:01.314 --> 18:02.533
Four.

18:02.576 --> 18:04.622
And there are 40
in there?

18:04.665 --> 18:06.319
So?

18:06.363 --> 18:08.713
So,
with that many people,

18:08.756 --> 18:10.889
all it takes
is one nervous guy

18:10.932 --> 18:13.457
with an itchy trigger finger
to set things off.

18:13.500 --> 18:15.894
I don't think
you appreciate --No, no, no, hold on.

18:15.937 --> 18:18.505
He's right. Alright, we've never
dealt with it, it's game over.

18:18.549 --> 18:23.467
Guys, it's not up
for discussion.

18:23.510 --> 18:26.296
I need you to trust
that I know what I'm doing.

18:26.339 --> 18:28.080
So, let's go.

18:28.124 --> 18:30.169
♪

18:30.213 --> 18:33.738
Fine.

18:33.781 --> 18:36.871
Hey, I need you
to wear that.

18:36.915 --> 18:38.743
It's part
of your, um...

18:38.786 --> 18:40.745
costume.

18:40.788 --> 18:43.965
♪

18:44.009 --> 18:47.143
This is how
this is going to go.

18:51.234 --> 18:58.937
♪

18:58.980 --> 19:01.505
Hello!

19:01.548 --> 19:04.421
My name is Aaron!

19:04.464 --> 19:07.250
We come from a community
called The Commonwealth.

19:07.293 --> 19:09.513
We'd like to extend
our friendship.

19:09.556 --> 19:16.346
♪

19:16.389 --> 19:19.262
Our people...

19:19.305 --> 19:23.527
left these where
you would find them.

19:23.570 --> 19:26.791
Since they're all gone,
I'm assuming you did.

19:26.834 --> 19:30.186
The chicken's
a little rubbery, but...

19:30.229 --> 19:32.623
it does the job.

19:32.666 --> 19:35.669
We have more back at our camp,
if you'd like.

19:35.713 --> 19:37.758
Is there anyone
I could speak with?

19:37.802 --> 19:39.543
Face-to-face?

19:39.586 --> 19:43.024
♪

19:43.068 --> 19:45.984
[Pounding]

19:46.027 --> 19:55.994
♪

19:56.037 --> 20:06.004
♪

20:06.047 --> 20:07.353
♪

20:07.397 --> 20:09.225
Weapons.

20:09.268 --> 20:19.235
♪

20:19.278 --> 20:29.245
♪

20:29.288 --> 20:38.776
♪

20:38.819 --> 20:40.081
♪

20:40.125 --> 20:42.258
Oh. Uh...

20:42.301 --> 20:44.521
It's kind of a bitch
to take off.

20:44.564 --> 20:49.482
♪

20:49.526 --> 20:51.876
Just the four of you?

20:51.919 --> 20:55.053
There's a group
of peacekeepers nearby,

20:55.096 --> 20:57.316
waiting for us
to check in.

20:57.360 --> 20:59.275
Sounds scary.

20:59.318 --> 21:09.285
♪

21:09.328 --> 21:18.903
♪

21:18.946 --> 21:28.913
♪

21:28.956 --> 21:38.923
♪

21:38.966 --> 21:40.533
♪

21:40.577 --> 21:42.927
Can't be too safe now,
can we?

21:42.970 --> 21:48.498
♪

21:48.541 --> 21:50.848
Last door
to the right.

21:50.891 --> 21:52.937
What's down there?

21:52.980 --> 22:02.947
♪

22:02.990 --> 22:12.957
♪

22:13.000 --> 22:22.967
♪

22:23.010 --> 22:32.977
♪

22:33.020 --> 22:42.987
♪

22:43.030 --> 22:47.208
♪

22:47.252 --> 22:49.385
[Knock on door]

22:49.428 --> 22:51.561
[Door creaks]

22:51.604 --> 23:01.571
♪

23:01.614 --> 23:04.661
♪

23:04.704 --> 23:06.227
Seats.

23:06.271 --> 23:09.535
♪

23:09.579 --> 23:11.755
[Door closes]

23:11.798 --> 23:21.765
♪

23:21.808 --> 23:26.596
♪

23:26.639 --> 23:28.467
I'm Aaron.

23:28.511 --> 23:30.208
And like
I said outside,

23:30.251 --> 23:33.037
we come from a community
called the Commonwealth.

23:33.080 --> 23:35.561
And it's, uh...

23:35.605 --> 23:38.608
Well, it's a bit
like the old world.

23:38.651 --> 23:40.392
50,000 people
live there.

23:40.436 --> 23:42.481
We have
a functioning government,

23:42.525 --> 23:45.005
protective walls,
housing for everyone,

23:45.049 --> 23:47.094
restaurants,
two movie theaters --

23:47.138 --> 23:49.749
Soldiers?

23:49.793 --> 23:52.012
And churches, too,
I take it.

23:52.056 --> 23:53.318
Eh, Father?

23:53.361 --> 23:55.494
Did you lose
your collar?

23:55.538 --> 23:57.453
Wanted you
to see whoI was

23:57.496 --> 23:59.890
before learning
whatI was.

23:59.933 --> 24:06.505
♪

24:06.549 --> 24:09.508
Okay.

24:09.552 --> 24:13.643
Let's say
this place is...

24:13.686 --> 24:15.253
like the old world,

24:15.296 --> 24:17.908
and they do have
a church,

24:17.951 --> 24:20.127
then they have to
have hookers, too.

24:20.171 --> 24:21.433
[Chuckles]

24:21.477 --> 24:24.175
Right?
And gambling?

24:24.218 --> 24:25.611
Shit side of town

24:25.655 --> 24:28.135
where addicts swap needles
with runaways.

24:28.179 --> 24:30.486
♪

24:30.529 --> 24:33.010
Got all that, too?

24:33.053 --> 24:34.533
♪

24:34.577 --> 24:36.666
I haven't seen
any of that.

24:36.709 --> 24:38.711
♪

24:38.755 --> 24:41.148
Aaron: Can I get
my bag back?

24:41.192 --> 24:42.802
I'd like
to show you something.

24:42.846 --> 24:48.025
♪

24:48.068 --> 24:50.941
[Door opens]

24:50.984 --> 24:56.903
♪

24:56.947 --> 25:00.472
[Door closes]

25:00.516 --> 25:02.300
Um...

25:02.343 --> 25:03.693
♪

25:03.736 --> 25:05.956
[Cellphone clicks]

25:05.999 --> 25:10.482
♪

25:10.526 --> 25:12.571
That's where we live.

25:12.615 --> 25:15.182
Whenever people see
those photos,

25:15.226 --> 25:17.402
they want
to live there, too.

25:17.445 --> 25:20.057
You'd just
let us in?

25:20.100 --> 25:21.493
That easy?

25:21.537 --> 25:24.322
No, it's not easy at all,
actually.

25:24.365 --> 25:26.890
Uh, there's
a screening process --

25:26.933 --> 25:29.327
An audition.

25:29.370 --> 25:31.851
Well, let me get
my tap-dancing shoes.

25:31.895 --> 25:34.767
[Laughs]

25:34.811 --> 25:38.292
Where is this,
uh...

25:38.336 --> 25:40.251
Commonwealth located?

25:40.294 --> 25:41.905
He can't
tell you that.

25:41.948 --> 25:43.602
Why?

25:43.646 --> 25:46.257
Because you say so?

25:46.300 --> 25:48.520
Yeah,
that's right.

25:48.564 --> 25:50.914
Then why
am I talking to him?

25:50.957 --> 25:55.745
♪

25:55.788 --> 25:59.357
Do me a favor,
fellas.

25:59.400 --> 26:01.620
Turn around
and look in that back corner.

26:01.664 --> 26:10.890
♪

26:10.934 --> 26:13.066
♪

26:13.110 --> 26:17.549
Those are raiders,
murderers,

26:17.593 --> 26:22.467
rapists,
and a few cannibals.

26:22.510 --> 26:23.990
♪

26:24.034 --> 26:27.690
All of them sat
in the same seats

26:27.733 --> 26:30.867
you're sitting in
right now.

26:30.910 --> 26:33.826
Most were wolves
dressed as sheep.

26:33.870 --> 26:37.787
All of them
meant my people harm.

26:37.830 --> 26:39.397
So...

26:39.440 --> 26:42.443
♪

26:42.487 --> 26:45.621
Mr. Head Wolf...

26:45.664 --> 26:46.839
if you know
where I live

26:46.883 --> 26:49.015
and I don't know
where you live,

26:49.059 --> 26:52.062
how dumb would that be
for me to let you go?

26:52.105 --> 26:54.455
♪

26:54.499 --> 26:56.414
What's your name?

26:56.457 --> 26:58.851
♪

26:58.895 --> 27:00.940
Toby Carlson.

27:00.984 --> 27:03.203
Toby...

27:03.247 --> 27:06.032
get on
your goddamn knees!

27:06.076 --> 27:09.166
Asses stay in
the goddamn chairs!

27:09.209 --> 27:11.603
♪

27:11.647 --> 27:14.214
Get on
your goddamn knees!

27:14.258 --> 27:16.390
Okay.
Answer the question.

27:16.434 --> 27:19.872
How dumb would I be
to let you go

27:19.916 --> 27:23.049
when you know
where my home is?

27:23.093 --> 27:25.008
It would be d-dumb,
okay?

27:25.051 --> 27:27.314
It'd be dumb.

27:27.358 --> 27:29.839
Yes,
it would!

27:29.882 --> 27:33.016
♪

27:33.059 --> 27:36.062
You know...

27:36.106 --> 27:38.717
you remind me of ol'
Billy Johnson.

27:38.761 --> 27:40.240
♪

27:40.284 --> 27:43.461
Billy came to us
a few years ago,

27:43.504 --> 27:46.856
with promises of great wealth
and prosperity

27:46.899 --> 27:49.336
in a land far away.

27:49.380 --> 27:53.123
But Billy wasn't gonna bring us
to any promised land.

27:53.166 --> 27:57.040
Billy just wanted to get us
out in the open

27:57.083 --> 28:00.608
so his raiders
could thoroughly kill us.

28:00.652 --> 28:03.829
Billy wound up
on the shelf

28:03.873 --> 28:07.485
because he thought
I was stupid.

28:07.528 --> 28:09.748
Do you think
I'm stupid, too?

28:09.792 --> 28:11.881
N-No!
No -- no -- no, I do not.

28:11.924 --> 28:14.405
Because I've got plenty of room
on the shelf

28:14.448 --> 28:15.711
right next to Billy!

28:15.754 --> 28:17.277
I-I don't want to be
on the shelf!

28:17.321 --> 28:18.670
And I don't think
you're stupid!

28:18.714 --> 28:20.280
Okay?!

28:20.324 --> 28:22.282
Tell me where
your raiding party is,

28:22.326 --> 28:25.242
or I'm gonna start
dropping bodies on the floor --

28:25.285 --> 28:26.678
starting with him!

28:26.722 --> 28:28.201
No!

28:28.245 --> 28:30.029
Hey!

28:30.073 --> 28:32.336
Do we look
like raiders to you?

28:32.379 --> 28:36.993
Wolves dressed as sheep,
speaking lies.

28:37.036 --> 28:38.951
♪

28:38.995 --> 28:41.475
None of you seem to have
any idea

28:41.519 --> 28:43.956
what
my responsibilities are

28:44.000 --> 28:47.568
to this place
and to my people.

28:47.612 --> 28:50.528
Has it occurred
to any of you

28:50.571 --> 28:52.530
that they
have entrusted me

28:52.573 --> 28:54.271
with their very souls?!

28:54.314 --> 28:56.229
Why did
you come here?!

28:56.273 --> 28:57.535
What you want?!

28:57.578 --> 28:58.884
Exactly!

28:58.928 --> 29:00.843
What do you have
that we would want?

29:00.886 --> 29:03.759
This place is a shithole!
Why would we want it?!

29:03.802 --> 29:05.108
The meat.

29:05.151 --> 29:07.327
You want the meat.

29:07.371 --> 29:09.460
You think
we're cannibals?

29:09.503 --> 29:12.898
Cannibals who came in
with prepackaged MREs?

29:12.942 --> 29:14.813
That's what
you're going with?

29:14.857 --> 29:18.730
All we've done
is given you food and water.

29:18.774 --> 29:21.602
You aren't starving right now
because of us!

29:21.646 --> 29:23.996
Is that real?
Or is that a lie?

29:24.040 --> 29:25.389
Gabriel: You know
what else is real?

29:25.432 --> 29:26.869
The soldiers
in those photos.

29:26.912 --> 29:28.392
If we don't get back,

29:28.435 --> 29:29.654
they'll come in here
and kill all of you.

29:29.697 --> 29:32.613
Or nobody dies,
okay?

29:32.657 --> 29:34.180
You save yourself

29:34.224 --> 29:36.443
and your people
by letting us go,

29:36.487 --> 29:38.837
and we will never
come back here again.

29:38.881 --> 29:40.839
We will never
bother you.

29:40.883 --> 29:43.146
I promise that,
okay?

29:43.189 --> 29:47.672
♪

29:47.715 --> 29:49.587
What a day.

29:49.630 --> 29:51.371
♪

29:51.415 --> 29:53.939
What a goddamn day.

29:53.983 --> 29:56.507
You will leave here.

29:56.550 --> 29:58.639
You will never
come back.

29:58.683 --> 30:00.119
And if --

30:00.163 --> 30:02.469
[Gunshots]

30:02.513 --> 30:04.732
♪

30:04.776 --> 30:06.909
Gabriel:
What did you do?

30:06.952 --> 30:08.171
My job.

30:08.214 --> 30:09.476
He was gonna
let us go!

30:09.520 --> 30:12.349
Shut up!

30:12.392 --> 30:14.003
Keep him hostage.

30:14.046 --> 30:15.613
And lock this door.

30:15.656 --> 30:17.833
I'll be back
when it's safe.

30:21.532 --> 30:28.844
♪

30:28.887 --> 30:31.324
[Birds chirping]

30:31.368 --> 30:34.458
[Knock on door]

30:34.501 --> 30:35.720
Yeah?

30:35.763 --> 30:37.200
Hey, bud.

30:37.243 --> 30:40.203
I got your...
call.

30:40.246 --> 30:42.466
What's up?

30:42.509 --> 30:44.903
Ah, no -- four years sober
next month.

30:44.947 --> 30:47.340
[Bottle thuds]

30:47.384 --> 30:48.907
[Sighs]

30:48.951 --> 30:51.910
What is wrong?

30:51.954 --> 30:53.303
You know how
I got Milton to agree

30:53.346 --> 30:54.695
to this whole
communal project

30:54.739 --> 30:56.045
with these hick towns
out in Virginia?

30:56.088 --> 30:57.829
Yeah.

30:57.873 --> 30:59.918
So she's released a lot
of resources for me.

30:59.962 --> 31:01.877
And I used
some of them

31:01.920 --> 31:04.270
to send out a convoy
full of supplies.

31:04.314 --> 31:05.881
For that other thing.

31:05.924 --> 31:07.665
Convoy didn't check in
last week,

31:07.708 --> 31:09.536
so I sent out scouts
to see what happened.

31:09.580 --> 31:10.798
It was hijacked.

31:10.842 --> 31:12.539
Troopers guarding it,
all dead.

31:12.583 --> 31:14.715
Oh, God.

31:14.759 --> 31:16.282
[Sighs]

31:16.326 --> 31:18.284
Who was it?

31:18.328 --> 31:20.460
Tracks led to
an apartment complex

31:20.504 --> 31:21.722
where some group
is holed up.

31:21.766 --> 31:23.376
Leader dresses like
a general.

31:23.420 --> 31:26.031
Another warlord.

31:26.075 --> 31:28.555
Followers are
religious, too.

31:28.599 --> 31:30.514
Mass on Tuesdays
andSundays.

31:30.557 --> 31:32.646
Cute.

31:32.690 --> 31:34.648
And they've got
your guns now.

31:34.692 --> 31:36.563
And the cargo, too,
I take it?

31:39.131 --> 31:41.264
Okay.
What am I missing?

31:41.307 --> 31:42.700
It's just
some warlord.

31:42.743 --> 31:44.310
Snuff them out.

31:44.354 --> 31:47.096
Assume the worst --
that the guns are pointing out

31:47.139 --> 31:49.272
of those top floors
in all directions.

31:49.315 --> 31:51.752
I send in a squad, they get cut
down before they hit the door.

31:51.796 --> 31:54.146
Then don't send a squad,
send a company.

31:54.190 --> 31:55.887
Then raze
the whole building.

31:55.931 --> 31:57.236
I ask
for a hundred troops,

31:57.280 --> 32:00.109
there's no way
Milton doesn't notice.

32:00.152 --> 32:02.720
"What happened,
Lance?

32:02.763 --> 32:04.548
This seems like
quite the misfire, Lance."

32:04.591 --> 32:09.379
No, I need
a surgical solution.

32:11.990 --> 32:14.340
Oh, man.

32:14.384 --> 32:16.386
I don't
do that anymore, Lance.

32:16.429 --> 32:17.648
Come on.

32:17.691 --> 32:19.345
I need
the former CIA guy

32:19.389 --> 32:20.781
who helped root out
disobedient shits from here

32:20.825 --> 32:22.000
back in the day.

32:22.044 --> 32:24.568
I need
an assassin.

32:24.611 --> 32:29.094
Listen,
I like being retired.

32:29.138 --> 32:33.490
I get up, I meditate,
then I get to go out

32:33.533 --> 32:35.753
and find people who need help
and give 'em a second chance.

32:35.796 --> 32:38.234
It's Zen.
It feels great.

32:38.277 --> 32:39.800
And it can be
taken from you.

32:39.844 --> 32:43.979
♪

32:44.022 --> 32:47.330
You, um...

32:47.373 --> 32:50.942
You tired of living,
Lance?

32:50.986 --> 32:52.161
♪

32:52.204 --> 32:54.163
Hmm?

32:54.206 --> 33:04.173
♪

33:04.216 --> 33:06.044
♪

33:06.088 --> 33:08.612
Most of the dead troopers
are kids in their 20s.

33:08.655 --> 33:11.049
♪

33:11.093 --> 33:14.052
That's on me.

33:14.096 --> 33:16.011
I need
to make it right.

33:16.054 --> 33:20.537
♪

33:20.580 --> 33:23.105
Okay.

33:23.148 --> 33:26.543
Okay.

33:26.586 --> 33:28.284
What are
you thinking?

33:28.327 --> 33:30.634
♪

33:30.677 --> 33:33.071
How's Aaron
working out?
He's great.

33:33.115 --> 33:34.377
He instantly connects
with people.

33:34.420 --> 33:36.335
Makes my job easy.
Great.

33:36.379 --> 33:38.033
Do you know about his buddy,
the priest?

33:38.076 --> 33:39.382
Stokes.

33:39.425 --> 33:40.774
Oh.

33:40.818 --> 33:42.254
Okay, okay.

33:42.298 --> 33:44.822
So we go in like we're making
first contact,

33:44.865 --> 33:46.389
and then,
since they are religious...

33:46.432 --> 33:49.261
Priest gets their guard down,
they let you in,

33:49.305 --> 33:52.656
go see the big chief,
and then...

33:52.699 --> 33:54.353
do what you do.

33:54.397 --> 33:56.094
And what about
when things turn

33:56.138 --> 33:58.314
and I have to tell them
what's what?

33:58.357 --> 34:00.272
They'll fall in line.

34:00.316 --> 34:02.405
Everyone does.

34:02.448 --> 34:06.887
♪

34:06.931 --> 34:09.238
Sweep the rear.

34:09.281 --> 34:16.114
♪

34:16.158 --> 34:19.900
The guns and the cargo
you hijacked.

34:19.944 --> 34:22.903
The ones that you massacred
my soldiers to get to,

34:22.947 --> 34:25.123
where are they?

34:25.167 --> 34:27.952
I got no idea
what you're talking about.

34:27.995 --> 34:37.875
♪

34:37.918 --> 34:40.269
Three sets of tracks
led back here from there.

34:40.312 --> 34:42.271
You wanna try again?

34:42.314 --> 34:43.881
♪

34:43.924 --> 34:46.275
Oh.

34:46.318 --> 34:49.147
That caravan.

34:49.191 --> 34:53.282
Yeah, we --
we found it like that.

34:53.325 --> 34:55.284
♪

34:55.327 --> 34:57.808
You just
lied to me.

34:57.851 --> 35:01.290
♪

35:01.333 --> 35:05.120
Hey! Hey!
Stop! Stop.

35:05.163 --> 35:06.730
Cuff him!

35:06.773 --> 35:14.172
♪

35:14.216 --> 35:15.913
Ian:
Hey, dickless.

35:15.956 --> 35:18.611
If I found those weapons,
don't you think I --

35:18.655 --> 35:19.917
[Gunshot]

35:19.960 --> 35:22.311
♪

35:22.354 --> 35:25.314
Ready the shelf,
warlord.

35:25.357 --> 35:28.317
Top shelf,
dead center.

35:28.360 --> 35:30.667
How's that sound?

35:30.710 --> 35:33.322
Right above Billy.

35:33.365 --> 35:35.019
♪

35:35.062 --> 35:36.368
Ooh!
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

35:36.412 --> 35:40.372
Hey!
Hey, where'd you go, huh?

35:40.416 --> 35:43.245
All that talk,
and you died so quick.

35:43.288 --> 35:48.554
♪

35:48.598 --> 35:51.340
[Screaming]

35:51.383 --> 35:55.170
♪

35:55.213 --> 35:58.782
[Panting]

35:58.825 --> 36:01.915
Don't you look at me
like that.

36:01.959 --> 36:04.266
He's a damn animal.

36:04.309 --> 36:06.616
We are supposed to
be helping people.

36:06.659 --> 36:08.444
We are.

36:08.487 --> 36:11.055
This is
the other side of it.

36:11.098 --> 36:14.145
Snuffing out threats.

36:14.189 --> 36:16.191
This is how
we make the world safe.

36:16.234 --> 36:18.236
♪

36:18.280 --> 36:21.065
[Horse neighs]

36:21.108 --> 36:22.806
Hold him.

36:22.849 --> 36:29.682
♪

36:29.726 --> 36:31.684
Pop him!

36:31.728 --> 36:32.990
[Gunshot]

36:33.033 --> 36:34.470
[Grunts]

36:34.513 --> 36:44.175
♪

36:44.219 --> 36:49.746
♪

36:49.789 --> 36:51.400
[Gun clicks]

36:51.443 --> 36:52.749
Oh.

36:52.792 --> 36:56.013
Interesting.

36:56.056 --> 36:57.754
Come on.
Let's go.

36:57.797 --> 36:59.756
♪

36:59.799 --> 37:02.672
[Gunshots]

37:02.715 --> 37:05.370
♪

37:05.414 --> 37:07.067
Do we follow?

37:07.111 --> 37:09.026
Daniels: Sir!

37:09.069 --> 37:14.074
♪

37:14.118 --> 37:16.599
I turn my back
for one goddamn minute!

37:16.642 --> 37:25.738
♪

37:25.782 --> 37:27.087
♪

37:27.131 --> 37:30.439
Get me my armor.

37:30.482 --> 37:33.529
He was a wolf,
just like their leader said.

37:33.572 --> 37:35.835
Think he was lying about
the stolen shipments?

37:35.879 --> 37:37.794
I don't know.

37:37.837 --> 37:40.449
What would the Commonwealth
want with all those guns?

37:40.492 --> 37:47.064
♪

37:47.107 --> 37:50.285
This the best way in?

37:50.328 --> 37:52.025
Yeah, but...

37:52.069 --> 37:53.549
where'd you get that?

37:53.592 --> 37:56.465
You gave it to the guy
who rode into Hilltop.

37:56.508 --> 37:58.641
No, I didn't.

37:58.684 --> 38:00.556
Then who did?

38:00.599 --> 38:03.950
♪

38:03.994 --> 38:07.476
[Horse neighs]

38:07.519 --> 38:09.478
Easy, girl.

38:09.521 --> 38:11.088
♪

38:11.131 --> 38:13.308
Negan:
Don't move.

38:13.351 --> 38:16.876
♪

38:16.920 --> 38:19.836
How many of you
are there?

38:19.879 --> 38:21.533
12.

38:21.577 --> 38:23.492
What are
they armed with?

38:23.535 --> 38:25.320
Machine guns.

38:25.363 --> 38:26.495
I didn't know.

38:26.538 --> 38:29.367
I didn't know.

38:29.411 --> 38:31.064
What's it look like?

38:31.108 --> 38:32.849
A lot dead.

38:32.892 --> 38:34.372
Guy in charge is arguing
with two others --

38:34.416 --> 38:37.027
a priest and a guy
with a spiked ball for an arm.

38:37.070 --> 38:38.202
Shit.

38:38.245 --> 38:39.943
Gabriel and Aaron.

38:39.986 --> 38:41.248
Jesse:
You know them?

38:41.292 --> 38:43.338
They didn't know,
either.

38:43.381 --> 38:45.165
We come from a place called
The Commonwealth.

38:45.209 --> 38:47.124
This isn't
what I signed up for.Shut up.

38:47.167 --> 38:48.473
Mm-hmm.

38:48.517 --> 38:55.741
♪

38:55.785 --> 38:58.353
There's a community
right here.

38:58.396 --> 39:00.137
You ask for Maggie,
no one else.

39:00.180 --> 39:03.488
You tell her Gabriel and Aaron
are in trouble.

39:03.532 --> 39:05.316
Go. Go!

39:05.360 --> 39:07.536
Uh-huh.

39:07.579 --> 39:10.365
♪

39:10.408 --> 39:13.150
Carlson: This is
the other side of it.

39:13.193 --> 39:16.327
Snuffing out threats.

39:16.371 --> 39:18.590
This is how we make
the world safe.

39:18.634 --> 39:21.071
[Horse neighs]

39:21.114 --> 39:30.646
♪

39:30.689 --> 39:36.478
♪

39:36.521 --> 39:37.740
Negan?

39:37.783 --> 39:39.742
Gabe.

39:39.785 --> 39:46.096
♪

39:46.139 --> 39:47.576
Carlson:
Interesting.Annie:
Two coming in.

39:47.619 --> 39:49.621
We gotta go!

39:49.665 --> 39:51.797
We gotta go!We can't leave him.

39:51.841 --> 39:53.408
If you go out there,
we all die.

39:53.451 --> 39:55.192
Come on.

39:55.235 --> 39:56.933
♪

39:56.976 --> 39:59.936
[Gunshots]

39:59.979 --> 40:02.417
Sir!

40:02.460 --> 40:07.247
♪

40:07.291 --> 40:09.424
I turn my back
for one goddamn minute!

40:13.515 --> 40:23.394
♪

40:23.438 --> 40:31.489
♪

40:31.533 --> 40:35.014
Residents of The Complex.

40:35.058 --> 40:39.845
You have been deemed
enemies of The Commonwealth.

40:39.889 --> 40:42.805
One of you
has stolen from us.

40:42.848 --> 40:46.199
That cannot stand.

40:46.243 --> 40:49.289
Bad news is,
your warlord is dead.

40:49.333 --> 40:54.947
The good news is,
you still can make things right.

40:54.991 --> 40:58.690
Gives us what's ours,
and we'll leave.

40:58.734 --> 41:00.083
That'll be that.

41:00.126 --> 41:02.520
Where are the weapons?I don't know.

41:02.564 --> 41:03.956
Then ask them --
quickly.

41:04.000 --> 41:06.872
Gabe, if she says
they don't have them,

41:06.916 --> 41:08.526
they don't have them.

41:08.570 --> 41:09.875
You don't understand.

41:09.919 --> 41:11.660
I'm praying
that you did steal them

41:11.703 --> 41:13.096
because without them,
we're dead.

41:13.139 --> 41:15.315
He's not gonna let any of us
leave here alive.

41:15.359 --> 41:25.282
♪

41:25.325 --> 41:28.677
Where are my weapons?

41:28.720 --> 41:31.854
I don't know.

41:31.897 --> 41:33.682
You really don't,
do you?

41:33.725 --> 41:35.901
No.

41:35.945 --> 41:37.729
Okay.

41:37.773 --> 41:39.122
I believe you.

41:39.165 --> 41:41.080
♪

41:41.124 --> 41:44.736
[Screaming]

41:44.780 --> 41:47.217
[Thud]

41:47.260 --> 41:50.220
♪

41:50.263 --> 41:53.876
And how about you?

41:53.919 --> 41:56.400
Hmm?

41:56.443 --> 41:59.621
[Screaming]

41:59.664 --> 42:00.926
[Thud]

42:00.970 --> 42:04.277
[Indistinct shouting, screaming]

42:04.321 --> 42:06.976
[Thud]

42:07.019 --> 42:10.762
[Indistinct shouting, screaming]

42:10.806 --> 42:12.503
[Thud]

42:12.547 --> 42:15.506
[Indistinct shouting, screaming]

42:15.550 --> 42:18.161
[Thud]

42:18.204 --> 42:20.642
♪

42:20.685 --> 42:23.340
Your people have let you down!

42:23.383 --> 42:26.561
♪

42:26.604 --> 42:28.563
Hit each room.

42:28.606 --> 42:30.390
Kill anyone
who won't talk.

42:30.434 --> 42:32.349
Copy that.

42:32.392 --> 42:37.223
♪

42:37.267 --> 42:41.880
What we need to do now
is stick together.

42:41.924 --> 42:43.839
You can forget about
giving up

42:43.882 --> 42:45.797
or begging
for forgiveness.

42:45.841 --> 42:48.408
Ian's dead.

42:48.452 --> 42:50.672
But he wasn't
our first leader.

42:50.715 --> 42:53.413
He wasn't what kept us
together this long.

42:53.457 --> 42:57.722
We did, and we did it
by working together as a family.

42:57.766 --> 42:59.550
And right now,
our family's scattered

42:59.594 --> 43:02.205
all over this building,
but you know what?

43:02.248 --> 43:05.991
We know this place better than
the assholes in our house do.

43:06.035 --> 43:08.603
We're coming
out of this on top.

43:08.646 --> 43:16.785
♪

43:16.828 --> 43:19.483
So that was,
um...

43:19.526 --> 43:21.659
That's pretty good.

43:21.703 --> 43:25.837
They -- They took out
our best.

43:25.881 --> 43:28.057
Yeah, but they needed
to hear it.

43:28.100 --> 43:30.363
♪

43:30.407 --> 43:32.801
Carlson: Hodges, come in.
Is the east end clear?

43:32.844 --> 43:37.588
♪

43:37.632 --> 43:39.416
Hodges, do you copy?

43:39.459 --> 43:42.201
♪

43:42.245 --> 43:43.638
Is the east end --

43:43.681 --> 43:53.343
♪

43:53.386 --> 43:54.649
♪

43:59.262 --> 44:02.918
Hornsby:
This place works because
everyone plays their part.

44:02.961 --> 44:07.052
If you can't or won't, that's
when the system breaks down.

44:07.096 --> 44:09.359
And we can't let that happen.

44:09.402 --> 44:12.144
♪

44:12.188 --> 44:16.192
We find our guns or we
burn this place to the ground.

44:16.235 --> 44:17.497
We have to get
these people out of here.

44:17.541 --> 44:20.457
[Walkers growling]

44:20.500 --> 44:22.198
[Grunts]

44:22.241 --> 44:23.547
That's a fight you ain't
gonna win.

44:23.590 --> 44:27.203
♪

44:28.030 --> 44:34.079
♪

44:34.123 --> 44:37.866
Why don't you want
their help?

44:37.909 --> 44:39.215
The Commonwealth's?

44:39.258 --> 44:42.261
♪

44:42.305 --> 44:44.699
Because we can get by
without it.

44:44.742 --> 44:46.570
Kang: One of the things
that we wanted to show

44:46.613 --> 44:50.574
is that there is like even like
a bit of a generational divide

44:50.617 --> 44:52.881
between how Maggie's looking
at everything versus

44:52.924 --> 44:55.710
how Lydia and Elijah
are looking at it.

44:55.753 --> 44:58.538
And I think, like,
you're seeing the after effects

44:58.582 --> 45:00.932
of somebody like Lydia
feeling like my mother

45:00.976 --> 45:03.761
had this point of view
that it's either us or them.

45:03.805 --> 45:07.809
And I think like she has kind
of come to the point of view

45:07.852 --> 45:10.507
that her mother
was in fact wrong.

45:10.550 --> 45:12.509
You think the Commonwealth
knows better?

45:12.552 --> 45:13.902
Is that crazy to think?

45:13.945 --> 45:15.468
Yes.

45:15.512 --> 45:18.994
Those people have not
been tested for 10 years.

45:19.037 --> 45:21.126
Do you wanna be there
when they are?

45:21.170 --> 45:25.130
I think for Maggie,
she is really feeling burned

45:25.174 --> 45:26.697
by the experiences she's had.

45:26.741 --> 45:29.918
She feels that their
resources are limited

45:29.961 --> 45:31.354
and their energy is limited.

45:31.397 --> 45:34.836
So why extend yourself
to help somebody

45:34.879 --> 45:36.489
when you have no idea
if you're just walking

45:36.533 --> 45:38.013
into a trap?

45:38.056 --> 45:40.667
What happened to taking in
whoever was in need?

45:40.711 --> 45:42.669
Being outnumbered has never
stopped you before.

45:42.713 --> 45:44.280
Maybe it should have.

45:44.323 --> 45:46.586
The Maggie that's underneath
all of that

45:46.630 --> 45:48.284
has a big heart.

45:48.327 --> 45:50.721
She's the one that kept
the doors of Hilltop open

45:50.765 --> 45:53.028
when Alexandria felt
they needed to close off.

45:53.071 --> 45:55.378
And so there is definitely
a part of her

45:55.421 --> 45:56.988
that would like
to get back to that,

45:57.032 --> 46:00.296
but she's struggling
with the experiences she had.

46:02.254 --> 46:05.083
God,
do you feel that?

46:05.127 --> 46:07.216
That rush?

46:07.259 --> 46:09.740
That mix of dopamine
and adrenaline, just...

46:09.784 --> 46:11.611
[Grunts]

46:11.655 --> 46:14.832
Kang: Carlson is one of these
guys that imagine

46:14.876 --> 46:20.185
he's really into like New Age
self-help mantras,

46:20.229 --> 46:23.710
and he's kind of
too much to handle.

46:23.754 --> 46:27.627
And Aaron is kind of saying
like, you know, he's a weirdo,

46:27.671 --> 46:30.456
but at the same time,
his heart is in the right place.

46:30.500 --> 46:32.589
We've been doing something
that is meaningful,

46:32.632 --> 46:34.417
and none of that is --
is false, by the way.

46:34.460 --> 46:37.028
Like, you know,
we find out in the flashback

46:37.072 --> 46:40.162
to when Carlson
and Hornsby talk.

46:40.205 --> 46:42.294
I like being retired.

46:42.338 --> 46:46.690
I get up, I meditate,
then I get to go out

46:46.733 --> 46:48.953
and find people who need help
and give 'em a second chance.

46:48.997 --> 46:50.607
It's Zen.

46:50.650 --> 46:52.609
Gabriel's a very good
judge of character, too.

46:52.652 --> 46:54.002
So he's kind of like,
"Who is this fool?"

46:54.045 --> 46:56.134
Like, "What are we dealing
with here?"

46:56.178 --> 46:58.441
And I think, like,
in very Gabriel's fashion,

46:58.484 --> 47:00.269
he has some pretty, like,
funny lines

47:00.312 --> 47:03.054
that Seth delivers
beautifully, as always.

47:03.098 --> 47:04.447
Abort?

47:04.490 --> 47:07.232
Just because of some
pre-game jitters?

47:07.276 --> 47:09.060
No, because your plan
is shit,

47:09.104 --> 47:10.496
and I don't want
to die.

47:10.540 --> 47:12.455
They're kind of saddled
with this guy

47:12.498 --> 47:14.283
that they think
is probably going to drive

47:14.326 --> 47:15.545
them down a little bit.

47:15.588 --> 47:24.771
♪

47:24.815 --> 47:26.773
Seats.

47:26.817 --> 47:30.125
Kang: When Aaron goes into
this situation, he feels like,

47:30.168 --> 47:32.736
wow, this is more intense
than we expected,

47:32.779 --> 47:36.435
but Aaron is very,
very good at disarming people

47:36.479 --> 47:39.438
and just kind of calmly
and cooly

47:39.482 --> 47:42.311
bringing the temperature down
and the situation.

47:42.354 --> 47:44.226
Aaron:
That's where we live.

47:44.269 --> 47:46.793
Whenever people see
those photos,

47:46.837 --> 47:48.491
they want to live there,
too.

47:48.534 --> 47:51.711
The point of distress
starts to happen

47:51.755 --> 47:54.453
when Carlson speaks up
in the meeting.

47:54.497 --> 47:56.238
Where is this,
uh...

47:56.281 --> 47:57.935
Commonwealth located?

47:57.979 --> 47:59.719
He can't
tell you that.

47:59.763 --> 48:01.069
Why?

48:01.112 --> 48:03.941
Because you say so?

48:03.985 --> 48:05.464
Yeah,
that's right.

48:05.508 --> 48:07.727
For Aaron,
what he doesn't expect

48:07.771 --> 48:09.686
is that this guy
is going to turn around

48:09.729 --> 48:11.601
and suddenly turn
into like Jason Bourne.

48:11.644 --> 48:14.299
You will leave her.

48:14.343 --> 48:15.735
You will never
come back again.

48:15.779 --> 48:17.041
And if --

48:17.085 --> 48:19.914
[Gunshots]

48:19.957 --> 48:23.395
He had realize that was
all like operative business,

48:23.439 --> 48:27.269
you know, and that in fact,
he was actually very scary

48:27.312 --> 48:28.487
underneath the weirdness.

48:28.531 --> 48:30.837
For Aaron and Gabriel,

48:30.881 --> 48:33.101
they just feel like we regret

48:33.144 --> 48:34.537
all the decisions we've made

48:34.580 --> 48:37.235
[laughing] over the last,
like, 48 hours.

48:37.279 --> 48:39.020
Negan: Don't move.

48:39.063 --> 48:43.024
♪

48:43.067 --> 48:45.374
How many of you
are there?

48:45.417 --> 48:47.854
So when we come across Negan,

48:47.898 --> 48:49.726
we're finding out
a lot of things about him,

48:49.769 --> 48:52.250
which is like,
he's part of this new community.

48:52.294 --> 48:55.297
Like, here's all this stuff
that is going on with him

48:55.340 --> 48:58.387
and that he's kind of like,
tried to like, start afresh.

48:58.430 --> 49:00.737
Right here.
You ask for Maggie, no one else.

49:00.780 --> 49:04.132
You tell her Gabriel and Aaron
are in trouble.

49:04.175 --> 49:06.786
Go. Go!
Uh-huh.

49:06.830 --> 49:09.876
I don't know how much he has,
like, completely changed,

49:09.920 --> 49:12.227
but I think that the journey
that Negan is on

49:12.270 --> 49:15.839
is trying to figure out who
he wants to be going forward.

49:15.882 --> 49:20.583
And I think he understands
and has not forgotten the fact

49:20.626 --> 49:25.414
that he has done some things
that have really hurt people.

49:25.457 --> 49:27.242
I'm just getting started.

49:27.285 --> 49:29.026
♪

49:29.070 --> 49:32.508
He's a social creature.
He does not do well on his own.

49:32.551 --> 49:35.119
We felt that was
very in character for him

49:35.163 --> 49:37.643
is that he's like,
I'm striking out on my own,

49:37.687 --> 49:39.428
and he immediately runs
into a group is like,

49:39.471 --> 49:40.995
"Hey, let me join up."

49:41.038 --> 49:43.432
And then he's like,
deeply within it already,

49:43.475 --> 49:46.739
you know, over the course
of like some months.

49:46.783 --> 49:49.090
Your people have let you down!

49:49.133 --> 49:52.745
♪

49:52.789 --> 49:54.617
Hit each room.

49:54.660 --> 49:56.314
Kill anyone
who won't talk.

49:56.358 --> 49:57.620
Copy that?

49:57.663 --> 50:03.539
♪

50:05.454 --> 50:15.290
♪

50:15.333 --> 50:25.300
♪

50:25.343 --> 50:35.310
♪

50:35.353 --> 50:39.575
♪
